#: ../../E/exec.rst:5
msgid "exec"
msgstr "exec"

#: ../../E/exec.rst:7
msgid "/eg·zek´/, /eks´ek/, n\\."
msgstr "/eg·zek´/, /eks´ek/, 名詞"

#: ../../E/exec.rst:10
msgid ""
"[Unix: from execute] Synonym for :ref:`chain`\\, derives from the "
":manpage:`exec(2)` call."
msgstr "[Unix:executeより] \\ :ref:`chain`\\ の同義語で、\\ :manpage:`exec(2)`\\ 呼び出しに由来する。"

#: ../../E/exec.rst:13
msgid ""
"[from executive] obs. The command interpreter for an :ref:`OS` (see "
":ref:`shell`\\); term esp. used around mainframes, and prob. : derived from "
"UNIVAC's archaic EXEC 2 and EXEC 8 operating systems."
msgstr ""
"[executiveより] 廃語。\\ :ref:`OS`\\ のコマンドインタプリタ(\\ :ref:`shell`\\ "
"を参照)。特にメインフレーム周りで使われ、おそらくUNIVACの古めかしいEXEC 2およびEXEC 8オペレーティングシステムに由来する。"

#: ../../E/exec.rst:19
msgid ""
"At IBM and VM/CMS shops, the equivalent of a shell command file (among "
"VM/CMS users)."
msgstr "IBMやVM/CMSの現場では、(VM/CMSユーザーの間で)シェルコマンドファイルに相当するもの。"

#: ../../E/exec.rst:21
msgid ""
"The mainstream ‘exec’ as an abbreviation for (human) executive is *not* "
"used. To a hacker, an ‘exec’ is always a program, never a person."
msgstr ""
"主流の(人間の)executiveの略語としての‘exec’は使われ\\ *ない*\\ "
"。ハッカーにとって、‘exec’は常にプログラムであり、決して人ではない。"
